<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.60.5-6_0001a" />

<opener>
<dateline>
<note>Skyrim Farm</note>

11-22-'69
</dateline>

<salute><hi rend="double underline">Dear Slade:</hi></salute>   
</opener>
<p>Yes, I know I should have written you sooner, and I'm sorry, because you <hi rend="underline">are</hi> dear to me, my friend. I have been lost in my autobiography and I've written no letters for some time &#8212; too long.</p>

<p>Slade, what <hi rend="underline">is</hi> the latest about <del><unclear>your</unclear></del> your book? <hi rend="underline">Why</hi> did the publisher

<pb facs="nei.j4c.60.5-6_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
<fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

suddenly balk? Did he give you a royalty contract, or did you subsidize the book?</p>

<p>I see now that I should have written the publisher. Should I still do so? I really want to help.</p>

<p>I've been having wonderful times with audiences <del/> of late. I had 1500 last week, and they gave me eight encores!</p>

<fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.60.5-6_0002"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

<p>We will drive down to Skyrim for Thanksgiving. I have come to feel strange to the place. A house without a dear woman in it is not <del/> much.</p>

<p>I do still love you.</p>

<p>Give my warm regards to Nita.</p>
<closer>
<signed>John Neihardt</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
